  • Method Details

    • addAmount

      public int addAmount(List<ElettronicDevice> elDev, List<ElettronicDevice> buyElDev, String ID, String amount)
      This method is used to add other quantities of electronic device.
      Parameters:
      elDev - It is the ElettronicDevice's list.
      buyElDev - It is list of ElettronicDevice for the employee to purchase.
      ID - It is the identification code of the product to be modified.
      amount - represents the quantity of the product that refers to the ID.
      Returns:
      Returns an integer:
      0 : if the addition of the quantity to the product was successful;
      1 : if the addition of the quantity of the product is a negative number;
      2 : if an appropriate value has not been entered when adding the quantity of the product;
      3 : if product ID is not present.
